### **5. Embedding Caching**

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\utils\GenerateEmbeddings.js` (lines 34-60, 8-9)

In-memory cache with TTL:
- **Max entries:** 250
- **TTL:** 10 minutes (600,000 ms)
- **Cache key:** Normalized text (title + body)
- **Purpose:** Avoid regenerating identical embeddings

```javascript
const getCachedEmbedding = (text) => {
    const cached = embeddingCache.get(text);
    if(!cached) return null;
    if(Date.now() > cached.expiresAt){
        embeddingCache.delete(text);
        return null;
    }
    return [...cached.embedding];
}
```

---

### **6. Embedding Usage**

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\sql\discovery.sql` (lines 1-123)

Embeddings are used for semantic search with pgvector cosine similarity:

```sql
-- Cosine similarity distance operator
1 - (j.embeddings <=> query_embedding) as similarity

-- IVFFlat index for fast similarity search
CREATE INDEX journals_embeddings_ivfflat_idx
ON public.journals
USING ivfflat (embeddings vector_cosine_ops)
```

**Related Posts Discovery** - composite scoring:
- 70% semantic similarity
- 15% engagement (views, likes, comments, bookmarks)
- 15% recency
- 15% penalty for same-author posts

