# RelatedPosts: Add CTA action buttons to cards

## Context

Related post cards are currently passive — click to navigate and nothing else. The user wants each card to drive action: write a response, quote-repost, or save. All three patterns already exist in the codebase and just need to be wired into the RelatedPosts cards.

## Files to modify

| File | What |
|---|---|
| `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.jsx` | Add action bar to cards, wire up all three CTAs, manage RepostModal + bookmark mutation + toast |
| `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.css` | Action bar styling, button styles, toast, responsive, updated skeleton |

No backend changes needed — all three actions use existing APIs.

## Changes

### 1. RelatedPosts.jsx — imports & hooks

Add to existing imports:
- `useState` from react
- `AnimatePresence` (already imported from framer-motion)
- `useAuth` from `../../../Context/useAuth`
- `useBookMarkMutation, useRepostMutation` from `../../../utils/useMutation`
- `RepostModal` from `../../RepostModal/RepostModal`

In the `RelatedPosts` component, add:
- `const { session, user, openAuthModal } = useAuth()`
- `const userId = user?.userData?.[0]?.id`
- `const mutationBookmark = useBookMarkMutation(session, userId)`
- `const [repostJournal, setRepostJournal] = useState(null)` — which post's RepostModal is open
- `const [toast, setToast] = useState('')` — feedback message

### 2. RelatedPosts.jsx — three action handlers

Define in `RelatedPosts` component and pass down to `RelatedPostCard`:

**Add your take** — navigates to `/home` with editor state:
```js
const handleAddTake = (post) => {
    if (!session) return openAuthModal();
    navigate('/home', {
        state: {
            openEditor: true,
            editorMode: 'text',
            initialTitle: `Re: ${post.title || 'Untitled'}`,
        }
    });
};
```

**Repost** — opens RepostModal (same pattern as ContentView line 580-587):
```js
const handleRepost = (post) => {
    if (!session) return openAuthModal();
    setRepostJournal({
        id: post.id,
        title: post.title,
        users: { id: post.user_id, name: post.user_name, image_url: post.user_image_url, badge: post.user_badge }
    });
};
```

**Save** — toggles bookmark (same pattern as ContentView line 212-247):
```js
const handleSave = async (post) => {
    if (!session) return openAuthModal();
    const res = await mutationBookmark.mutateAsync({ journalId: post.id });
    showToast(res?.message === 'success' ? 'Saved to bookmarks' : 'Removed from bookmarks');
};
```

Toast helper:
```js
const toastRef = useRef();
const showToast = (msg) => {
    setToast(msg);
    clearTimeout(toastRef.current);
    toastRef.current = setTimeout(() => setToast(''), 2500);
};
```

### 3. RelatedPosts.jsx — RelatedPostCard action bar

Pass `onAddTake`, `onRepost`, `onSave`, and `currentUserId` as props.

Below `.rp-card-meta`, add an action bar:

```jsx
<div className="rp-card-actions">
    <button className="rp-action-btn" onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onAddTake(post); }}>
        {/* pen/write SVG icon */}
        <span className="rp-action-label">Your take</span>
    </button>
    {post.user_id !== currentUserId && (
        <button className="rp-action-btn" onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onRepost(post); }}>
            {/* repost SVG icon */}
            <span className="rp-action-label">Repost</span>
        </button>
    )}
    <button className="rp-action-btn" onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onSave(post); }}>
        {/* bookmark SVG icon */}
        <span className="rp-action-label">Save</span>
    </button>
</div>
```

Each button uses `e.stopPropagation()` so clicking an action doesn't also navigate to the post.

SVG icons: small inline SVGs (16px), matching the existing icon style from PostCards/ContentView. Pen icon for "Your take", loop-arrows for "Repost", bookmark for "Save".

### 4. RelatedPosts.jsx — RepostModal + toast rendering

At the bottom of the `RelatedPosts` return, after `.rp-grid`:

```jsx
{repostJournal && (
    <RepostModal
        journal={repostJournal}
        onClose={(result) => {
            setRepostJournal(null);
            if (result === 'success') showToast('Post was reposted');
        }}
    />
)}

<AnimatePresence>
    {toast && (
        <motion.div className="rp-toast" initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }} transition={{ duration: 0.2 }}>
            {toast}
        </motion.div>
    )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

### 5. RelatedPosts.css — action bar styles

```css
.rp-card-actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
}

.rp-action-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
}

.rp-action-btn:hover {
    background: var(--bg-hover);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.rp-action-btn svg {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}
```

### 6. RelatedPosts.css — toast

```css
.rp-toast {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 2rem;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    z-index: 1000;
    white-space: nowrap;
}
```

### 7. RelatedPosts.css — responsive (480px)

Hide action labels on small screens, show icons only:
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .rp-action-label { display: none; }
    .rp-action-btn { padding: 0.25rem; }
}
```

### 8. Skeleton height update

Bump `.rp-skeleton-card` height from `82px` → `106px` to account for the action bar.

## Verification

1. Open a post with related posts
2. Each card shows: title, excerpt, author/date, then a separator line with 3 action buttons
3. **Your take** — navigates to `/home` and opens the editor with title pre-filled as `Re: {title}`
4. **Repost** — opens RepostModal with the correct post data; hidden on own posts
5. **Save** — toggles bookmark, shows toast confirmation
6. All three actions require auth (opens auth modal if not logged in)
7. Clicking an action button does NOT navigate to the post (stopPropagation works)
8. Toast appears and auto-dismisses after 2.5s
9. On mobile (480px), action labels hide — only icons remain

